Reasoning: The paper describes the development of a neural network for medical diagnosing, which involves the use of sensors and questionnaire responses to generate signals and excite neurons. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category, which deals with the development and application of neural networks and other computational models inspired by biological systems. Additionally, the use of synaptic weights and likelihood ratios to estimate the reliability of the diagnosis suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The focus on medical applications and patient questionnaires suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) and Cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-categories.
